---
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import {
  raaricleElements,
  failurePatterns,
  captureVectors,
  structuralPrinciples,
} from "@data/reforms";
---

<PageLayout
  title="Diagnostic Frameworks"
  description="The analytical lens used across GovCompass to diagnose institutional failure and design reform: the RAARICLE™ framework, the five failure patterns, the capture vulnerability assessment, and the structural principles that inform every reform in the programme."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <header class="mb-10">
    <p class="font-heading text-sm font-semibold text-compass-green uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">
      Reform Toolkit
    </p>
    <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-3 leading-tight">
      Diagnostic Frameworks
    </h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Reform begins with diagnosis. Before recommending any institutional change, GovCompass tests it
      against four diagnostic frameworks — each of which surfaces a different dimension of governance failure
      and a different set of design principles for fixing it.
    </p>
    <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      These frameworks are the <strong class="text-text-primary">analytical scaffolding</strong> behind the
      <a href="/real-steps-to-reform" class="text-compass-green hover:underline font-semibold">Reform Roadmap</a> and
      the <a href="/reform-scorecard" class="text-compass-green hover:underline font-semibold">Reinforcing Cycle Scorecard</a>.
      Use them to evaluate any institution — a department, a municipality, an SOE, or a regulator — and to
      decide whether a proposed reform actually addresses the structural problem.
    </p>
  </header>

  <!-- On-page navigation -->
  <nav class="mb-10 flex flex-wrap gap-x-4 gap-y-1 text-xs font-heading" aria-label="Jump to section">
    <span class="text-text-secondary font-semibold">Jump to:</span>
    <a href="#raaricle" class="text-compass-green hover:underline">RAARICLE Framework</a>
    <a href="#failure-patterns" class="text-compass-green hover:underline">Failure Patterns</a>
    <a href="#capture-vectors" class="text-compass-green hover:underline">Capture Vectors</a>
    <a href="#structural-principles" class="text-compass-green hover:underline">Structural Principles</a>
  </nav>

  <!-- RAARICLE™ Framework -->
  <section id="raaricle" class="mb-12 scroll-mt-32" aria-label="RAARICLE diagnostic framework">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-2">
      The RAARICLE™ Framework
    </h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mb-6 leading-relaxed">
      Every institutional reform in the programme is diagnosed against eight governance elements.
      When any element is missing or misallocated, the institution cannot deliver — regardless of who
      is in charge, how much it is funded, or how clear its mandate appears on paper.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-6">
      {raaricleElements.map((el) => (
        <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden group">
          <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 cursor-pointer list-none [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden select-none hover:bg-bg-secondary transition-colors">
            <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-compass-green text-white font-heading font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
              {el.letter}
            </span>
            <span class="font-heading text-sm font-semibold text-text-primary">
              {el.name}
            </span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-text-secondary shrink-0 ml-auto transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-3 pt-1 border-t border-gray-100">
            <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">{el.question}</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      For the foundational essay introducing this diagnostic, see
      <a href="/articles/ra-1-1-eight-tests" class="text-compass-green hover:underline font-semibold">The Eight Tests</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Failure Patterns -->
  <section id="failure-patterns" class="mb-12 scroll-mt-32" aria-label="Failure patterns">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-2">
      Five Failure Patterns
    </h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mb-6 leading-relaxed">
      When the RAARICLE™ framework is violated, one of five recurring failure patterns results. Each
      pattern has a distinct structural signature and a distinct corrective intervention.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-3">
      {failurePatterns.map((fp, i) => (
        <a
          href={`/articles/${fp.articleSlug}`}
          class="border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4 bg-red-50/40 hover:border-red-300 hover:bg-red-50/60 transition-colors group block"
        >
          <p class="font-heading text-sm font-bold text-red-800 mb-1 group-hover:text-red-900">
            {i + 1}. {fp.name}
          </p>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">{fp.description}</p>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Capture Vectors -->
  <section id="capture-vectors" class="mb-12 scroll-mt-32" aria-label="Capture Vulnerability Assessment Framework">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-2">
      The Capture Vulnerability Assessment Framework
    </h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mb-6 leading-relaxed">
      Five vectors through which institutions are captured. Capture-resistant institutional design must address
      all five simultaneously — vulnerabilities in any one vector are exploited and propagate. Each vector has
      a corresponding structural defence built into the reform programme.
    </p>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      {captureVectors.map((cv) => (
        <details class="border border-amber-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden group bg-amber-50/30">
          <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 cursor-pointer list-none [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden select-none hover:bg-amber-50/60 transition-colors">
            <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-amber-700 text-white font-heading font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
              {cv.number}
            </span>
            <span class="font-heading text-sm font-semibold text-text-primary flex-1">
              Vector {cv.number}: {cv.name}
            </span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-text-secondary shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 pt-1 border-t border-amber-200 space-y-3">
            <div>
              <p class="font-heading text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-amber-800 mb-1">How it works</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">{cv.description}</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-heading text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-compass-green mb-1">Structural defences</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">{cv.defences}</p>
            </div>
            <a
              href={`/articles/${cv.articleSlug}`}
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-xs font-heading font-semibold text-compass-green hover:text-compass-green-dark hover:underline transition-colors"
            >
              Read the full vector analysis
              <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" aria-hidden="true">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
              </svg>
            </a>
          </div>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Structural Principles -->
  <section id="structural-principles" class="mb-12 scroll-mt-32" aria-label="Structural principles">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-2">
      Structural Principles Informing Institutional Reforms
    </h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary mb-6 leading-relaxed">
      These principles cut across every workstream and every reform. They are the design rules that any
      proposed institutional arrangement must satisfy — together they describe what a capture-resistant,
      delivery-capable institution looks like.
    </p>
    <div class="space-y-2">
      {structuralPrinciples.map((sp, i) => (
        <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden group">
          <summary class="flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 cursor-pointer list-none [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden select-none hover:bg-bg-secondary transition-colors">
            <span class="w-6 h-6 rounded bg-compass-green-light text-compass-green font-heading font-bold text-xs flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
              {i + 1}
            </span>
            <span class="font-heading text-sm font-semibold text-text-primary">
              {sp.title}
            </span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-text-secondary shrink-0 ml-auto transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-3 pt-1 border-t border-gray-100 space-y-2">
            <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">{sp.description}</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed"><span class="font-semibold text-text-primary">Example areas:</span> {sp.examples}</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Gateway -->
  <section class="mb-8" aria-label="Where to go from here">
    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">
      Where to go from here
    </h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
      The frameworks above are diagnostic. They tell you whether an institution is structurally sound.
      The pages below put them to work — translating diagnosis into a sequenced reform programme and a
      measurement system that tracks whether the programme is delivering.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <a
        href="/real-steps-to-reform"
        class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5 hover:border-compass-green hover:shadow-md transition-all group"
      >
        <p class="font-heading text-base font-bold text-text-primary group-hover:text-compass-green transition-colors mb-2">
          Reform Roadmap
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          80+ concrete reforms across four workstreams, sequenced over 10 years, with the legislative changes required to implement them.
        </p>
      </a>
      <a
        href="/reform-scorecard"
        class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5 hover:border-compass-green hover:shadow-md transition-all group"
      >
        <p class="font-heading text-base font-bold text-text-primary group-hover:text-compass-green transition-colors mb-2">
          Reinforcing Cycle Scorecard
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          The 15 indicators across safety, growth, and development that show whether the reform programme is producing systemic change.
        </p>
      </a>
      <a
        href="/articles/ra-1-1-eight-tests"
        class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5 hover:border-compass-green hover:shadow-md transition-all group"
      >
        <p class="font-heading text-base font-bold text-text-primary group-hover:text-compass-green transition-colors mb-2">
          The Eight Tests
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          The foundational essay that introduces the RAARICLE&#8482; framework and explains how the eight elements interact.
        </p>
      </a>
      <a
        href="/articles/ra-5-2-anti-capture-architecture"
        class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5 hover:border-compass-green hover:shadow-md transition-all group"
      >
        <p class="font-heading text-base font-bold text-text-primary group-hover:text-compass-green transition-colors mb-2">
          The Anti-Capture Architecture
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          The deep-dive on the five capture vectors — political, commercial, labour, regulatory, information — and the structural defences against each.
        </p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
